1
00:00:05,770 --> 00:00:08,130
You have got to try this cheesecake.
你得试试这块起司蛋糕

2
00:00:08,370 --> 00:00:11,100
You know, I'm not that much of a sweet tooth..
我不是那么喜欢吃甜食…

3
00:00:12,440 --> 00:00:14,640
Oh, my God, it's so creamy!
我的天啊，它好香浓

4
00:00:15,180 --> 00:00:18,010
That's the best cheesecake I've ever had!
那是我吃过最棒的起司蛋糕！

5
00:00:18,280 --> 00:00:19,940
Where did you get this?
你在哪里买到它？

6
00:00:20,620 --> 00:00:24,450
It was at the front door when I got home. Somebody sent it to us.
我回家时它就已经放在门口了 有人把它寄给我们

7
00:00:25,490 --> 00:00:27,180
This isn't addressed to you.
收件人不是你

8
00:00:27,460 --> 00:00:30,690
This is addressed to Mrs. Braverman downstairs!
收件人是楼下的布雷曼太太！

9
00:00:30,930 --> 00:00:32,390
Thief!
小偷！

10
00:00:33,400 --> 00:00:35,760
I didn't read the box before I opened it...
我没看收件人姓名就打开了盒子…

11
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:38,630
and you can't return a box after you opened it!
盒子已经打开了就无法退还！

12
00:00:38,830 --> 00:00:41,960
-Why not? -Because it's too delicious!
-为什么？ -因为它太好吃了

13
00:00:43,710 --> 00:00:46,200
You stole this cheesecake. That's wrong.
你偷了这个起司蛋糕，那是不对的

14
00:00:46,470 --> 00:00:51,040
No, it'll be okay because Mrs. Braverman will send for a free one.
不，没关系的，因为布雷曼太太 会免费再收到一个

15
00:00:51,280 --> 00:00:53,010
That way, we all win.
那可是双赢的局面

16
00:00:53,210 --> 00:00:57,170
The only losers are the big cheesecake conglomerate...
唯一的输家是大型起司蛋糕店…

17
00:00:57,490 --> 00:00:59,920
"Mama's Little Bakery."
“小妈妈的面包店”

18
00:01:00,920 --> 00:01:02,510
I feel terrible.
我觉得好难过

19
00:01:02,790 --> 00:01:05,230
I'm a horrible, horrible person.
我是个大坏蛋

20
00:01:06,560 --> 00:01:08,220
I'm sorry, what?
对不起，你说什么？

21
00:01:09,930 --> 00:01:12,160
The One With All The Cheesecakes
本集播出：起司蛋糕

00:01:13,930 --> 00:01:15,160
rainystar压制iPod-MP4

22
00:01:49,770 --> 00:01:52,260
I should get going. Big day at work.
我得走了，我今天工作很忙

23
00:01:52,470 --> 00:01:54,640
You know how I'm in a coma?
你们知道我怎么会昏迷不醒吗？

24
00:01:55,040 --> 00:01:58,740
Today they do a test on me and it turns out I'm not brain-dead.
今天他们要帮我做检查 结果发现我没有脑死

25
00:01:59,710 --> 00:02:00,840
So..
所以…

26
00:02:01,050 --> 00:02:02,640
Mr. Smarty Pants.
聪明先生

27
00:02:02,850 --> 00:02:05,250
It's just my character that's not brain-dead.
没有脑死的是我演的角色

28
00:02:06,320 --> 00:02:08,150
Phoebe, still on for tonight?
菲比，今晚的事没取消吧？

29
00:02:08,390 --> 00:02:10,650
-Absolutely. -I'll see you at 8.
-当然 -八点见

30
00:02:10,860 --> 00:02:12,450
What's at 8?
什么东西八点见？

31
00:02:12,690 --> 00:02:17,560
Dinner. We get together about once a month to discuss the rest of you.
我们约好吃晚餐，我们大约 一个月会约一次去讨论你们的事

32
00:02:19,200 --> 00:02:21,000
Wow! Did not know that.
哇！我真的不知道

33
00:02:21,240 --> 00:02:23,760
May I say how lovely you look today?
我能说你今天看起来很漂亮吗？

34
00:02:24,010 --> 00:02:25,030
Duly noted.
那当然

35
00:02:26,340 --> 00:02:30,610
zSo for tomorrow, do you want to rent a car and drive down together?
明天你要租辆车一起开过去吗？

36
00:02:30,910 --> 00:02:34,400
-What are you talking about? -Cousin Frannie's wedding.
-你在说什么？ -芬妮表妹的婚礼

37
00:02:35,220 --> 00:02:37,840
You were invited?
你被邀请了？

38
00:02:38,990 --> 00:02:40,550
No.
不

39
00:02:40,760 --> 00:02:43,050
Oh, my God, I can't believe this.
我的天啊，我不敢相信

40
00:02:43,360 --> 00:02:45,760
I thought only Mom and Dad were invited.
我以为他们只邀请了爸跟妈

41
00:02:45,990 --> 00:02:50,120
From the ages of 7 to 9,  Frannie and I were inseparable.
七岁到九岁，芬妮跟我形影不离

42
00:02:50,370 --> 00:02:54,170
Maybe since the age of 9,  Frannie's made some new friends.
或许九岁后，芬妮交了新朋友

43
00:02:55,500 --> 00:02:58,870
It's probably just a mistake. Let me call Aunt Cheryl.
或许这只是个误会 我打电话去问雪若阿姨

44
00:02:59,140 --> 00:03:02,510
Maybe you are invited and the invitation got lost in the mail.
或许他们邀请你了，只是请帖寄丢了

45
00:03:02,710 --> 00:03:05,770
You call her and tell her that when we were kids...
你可以打电话告诉她，我们小时候…

46
00:03:05,980 --> 00:03:09,280
her precious Frannie tried to undress me several times.
她的宝贝芬妮好几次想脱光我的衣服

47
00:03:09,520 --> 00:03:13,010
If I hadn't stopped her, there wouldn't be a wedding to go to.
要不是我阻止了她，她也结不了婚

48
00:03:13,220 --> 00:03:15,950
She tried to undress me too.
她也想脱我的衣服

49
00:03:16,590 --> 00:03:19,250
I used to undress my cousin Glenn.
我以前会帮葛兰表弟脱衣服

50
00:03:26,570 --> 00:03:30,530
Joseph Francis Tribbiani, are you home yet?
乔瑟夫法兰西斯崔比亚尼 你回家了吗？

51
00:03:31,010 --> 00:03:33,000
I think he's still out. What's wrong?
我想他还没有回家，怎么了？

52
00:03:33,240 --> 00:03:35,610
I'll tell you, Rachel Karen Greene.
我得告诉你，瑞秋凯伦葛林

53
00:03:35,840 --> 00:03:38,840
I had plans with Joey, and he left me this note.
我跟乔伊有约，他留了这张字条给我

54
00:03:39,150 --> 00:03:42,550
"Phoebe, can't make it. Got a date. Talk to you later.
菲比，我没办法赴约 我有约会，待会再谈

55
00:03:42,750 --> 00:03:44,410
"Big Daddy."
大爹地

56
00:03:45,420 --> 00:03:48,410
-"Big Daddy"? -That's a nickname we were trying.
-“大爹地”？ -那是我们之间的昵称

57
00:03:48,690 --> 00:03:52,990
You know what nickname never caught on? "The Ross-a-tron."
你知道什么样的昵称，不会跟 别人重覆吗？“罗斯原子超人”

58
00:03:56,660 --> 00:03:58,690
Here's Joseph Francis!
乔瑟夫法兰西斯回来了！

59
00:03:58,930 --> 00:04:02,160
Wait, what are you middle-naming me for?
等一下，你干嘛叫我的全名？

60
00:04:02,370 --> 00:04:03,840
I left you a note.
我留了字条给你

61
00:04:04,040 --> 00:04:06,370
That doesn't give you the right to ditch me!
那不是你放我鸽子的好理由

62
00:04:06,640 --> 00:04:10,540
You can cancel plans with friends if there's a possibility for sex.
如果你有机会上床 当然可以取消跟朋友的约会

63
00:04:10,780 --> 00:04:12,710
He's right. That is the rule.
他说的对，这是规则

64
00:04:12,950 --> 00:04:16,750
I don't accept it. When we make plans, I expect you to show up.
我无法接受这种事 我们约好后，我期待你会出现

65
00:04:16,950 --> 00:04:20,180
I'm not a way to kill time till you meet someone better.
我不是你泡到马子前 打发时间的代替品

66
00:04:20,420 --> 00:04:25,050
Boyfriends and girlfriends will come and go, but this is for life.
男女朋友来来去去 但朋友是一辈子的

67
00:04:25,360 --> 00:04:29,350
I'm so sorry. I had no idea it would bother you this much.
我真的很抱歉，我不知道 这对你来说那么重要

68
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:30,930
Well, it does.
喔，它的确很重要

69
00:04:31,170 --> 00:04:33,290
Well, can I make it up to you?
我可以弥补你吗？

70
00:04:33,570 --> 00:04:34,800
I'm sorry.
对不起

71
00:04:35,070 --> 00:04:38,970
How about dinner tomorrow night? I'll pay for myself.
明天晚上一起吃饭吧？我会自己付钱

72
00:04:41,410 --> 00:04:43,240
Okay, you wore me down.
好吧，你说服了我

73
00:04:45,110 --> 00:04:49,280
While you're over there, how about a beer for "The Ross-a-tron"?
既然你站在那边，拿罐啤酒给 “罗斯原子超人”吧？

74
00:04:50,550 --> 00:04:52,490
"Ross.." Is that back?
“罗斯…”，它又回来了？

75
00:04:58,230 --> 00:05:00,060
The other cheesecake came.
又有起司蛋糕

76
00:05:00,300 --> 00:05:02,700
They delivered it here again.
他们又把它送到这里来

77
00:05:03,600 --> 00:05:06,400
Just bring it downstairs. What's the problem?
把它送到楼下去，那有什么问题？

78
00:05:06,600 --> 00:05:08,590
I can't seem to say goodbye.
我不知道该怎么说再见

79
00:05:08,840 --> 00:05:10,130
Are you serious?
你是说真的吗？

80
00:05:10,340 --> 00:05:13,600
We ate an entire cake two days ago and you want more?
两天前我们吃掉 一个蛋糕，你还想再吃？

81
00:05:13,840 --> 00:05:16,470
Well, I've forgotten what it tastes like.
喔，我已经忘记它的味道了

82
00:05:16,740 --> 00:05:19,610
It was cheesecake. It was fine.
它是起司蛋糕，它很好吃

83
00:05:19,850 --> 00:05:23,720
It had a buttery, crumbly, graham cracker crust...
它有又香又浓，酥酥的饼干…

84
00:05:23,920 --> 00:05:26,750
with a very rich...
还有非常浓郁…

85
00:05:26,990 --> 00:05:30,820
yet light cream cheese filling.
但不油腻的奶油起司

86
00:05:33,160 --> 00:05:35,530
Wow, my whole mouth just filled with saliva.
我的嘴巴全是口水

87
00:05:36,530 --> 00:05:39,230
Know what? Forget it. We're just hungry.
你知道吗？忘了它，我们只是饿了

88
00:05:39,430 --> 00:05:41,930
We haven't had lunch. We're just lightheaded.
我们没有吃午餐，所以头昏脑胀

89
00:05:42,170 --> 00:05:45,660
So let's go have lunch and forget about the cheesecake.
我们去吃午餐，忘了那个起司蛋糕吧

90
00:05:45,940 --> 00:05:48,310
We'll drop it off so we're not tempted.
我们得把它还回去，才不会被诱惑

91
00:05:48,510 --> 00:05:51,770
-Where do you want to eat? -Mama's Little Bakery, Chicago.
-你要去哪里吃午餐？ -芝加哥小妈妈面包店

92
00:05:56,950 --> 00:05:59,480
Mei Torme died.
梅尔多米死了

93
00:05:59,750 --> 00:06:02,310
Joey, that paper's like a year old.
乔伊，那是一年前的报纸

94
00:06:02,520 --> 00:06:06,020
Does that mean the Sam Goody's sale is over?
那表示山姆古迪商店 的大特卖结束了？

95
00:06:09,330 --> 00:06:12,130
So, I finally heard back from Aunt Cheryl...
我终于收到雪若阿姨的回音…

96
00:06:12,370 --> 00:06:14,890
and apparently it wasn't a mistake.
很明显地这不是误会

97
00:06:15,170 --> 00:06:16,900
There's limited seating..
婚礼现场座位有限…

98
00:06:17,170 --> 00:06:21,870
Limited seating? I am just one tiny person!
座位有限？我是个瘦皮猴！

99
00:06:22,710 --> 00:06:24,700
Yeah, but she doesn't know that.
对，但是她不知道

100
00:06:24,980 --> 00:06:27,500
I mean, the last time she saw you...
我是说上次她看到你…

101
00:06:27,780 --> 00:06:31,810
you'd have turned one of those little wedding chairs into kindling.
你会把婚礼用的小椅子给压垮

102
00:06:33,650 --> 00:06:36,320
"Limited seating." That's such a lame excuse.
“座位有限”那真是个烂借口

103
00:06:36,520 --> 00:06:39,080
That's not the reason she's not inviting me.
那不是她不邀请我的原因

104
00:06:39,360 --> 00:06:43,160
What's the big deal? I wasn't invited to the ceremony, just the reception.
那有什么大不了的呢？ 我没办法观礼，只能去吃喜酒

105
00:06:43,400 --> 00:06:47,800
If it makes you feel any better, Joan and I will just make an appearance...
如果这能让你觉得开心一点 琼安跟我只会去亮个相…

106
00:06:48,040 --> 00:06:51,330
and then we'll leave early as a sign of protest.
我们会提早离开，以示抗议

107
00:06:51,540 --> 00:06:53,910
-Joan? -Yeah, my date.
-琼安？ -对，她是我的女伴

108
00:06:54,110 --> 00:06:58,170
Assistant professor in linguistics. Tall, very beautiful.
她是语言学系的助教，又高又漂亮

109
00:06:58,410 --> 00:07:02,750
And despite what some people say,  not broad-backed.
虽然有些人说，别挑太魁梧的女孩

110
00:07:03,750 --> 00:07:06,950
Wait a minute. You got "Ross Geller and Guest"?
等一下，你收到的喜帖 是“请携伴参加”？

111
00:07:07,220 --> 00:07:09,420
I wasn't invited,  and you got "and Guest"?
我没有被邀请 你却可以“携伴参加”？

112
00:07:09,620 --> 00:07:12,750
Excuse me, I do have to interrupt on Ross' behalf.
对不起，我真的得解释罗斯的行为

113
00:07:13,030 --> 00:07:14,930
I think the rule applies here.
我想规则也适用在这里

114
00:07:15,130 --> 00:07:17,360
Since he has a chance to get on broad-back..
因为他有机会跟魁梧女人上床…

115
00:07:17,600 --> 00:07:18,900
Not broad-back!
她没有那么魁梧！

116
00:07:20,440 --> 00:07:22,900
Wait a minute. You're bringing me.
等一下，你得带我去

117
00:07:23,140 --> 00:07:24,700
I can't cancel on Joan.
我不能放琼安鸽子

118
00:07:24,940 --> 00:07:26,930
-Why not? -Did you not hear me?
-为什么？ -你没有听到吗？

119
00:07:27,140 --> 00:07:30,980
She's an assistant professor in the linguistics department.
她是语言学系的助教

120
00:07:31,250 --> 00:07:33,210
They're wild.
她们很辣

121
00:07:33,880 --> 00:07:37,150
-Why do you want to come anyway? -Because...
-你到底为什么想去？ -因为…

122
00:07:37,420 --> 00:07:38,940
she's my cousin.
她是我表妹

123
00:07:39,220 --> 00:07:41,980
I mean, we grew up together.
我们是一起长大的

124
00:07:42,260 --> 00:07:46,060
Family, you know? And all that's important to me.
我们是家人，你知道吗？ 对我来说那很重要

125
00:07:46,730 --> 00:07:49,250
Okay, all right. I'll take you.
好吧，我带你去

126
00:07:49,500 --> 00:07:51,230
I'll go call Joan.
我去打电话给琼安

127
00:07:52,430 --> 00:07:54,060
Oh, that's nice.
那真的是太棒了

128
00:07:54,270 --> 00:07:56,070
Family should be there.
家人应该要出席的

129
00:07:56,300 --> 00:07:58,470
It's her wedding. Happiest day of her life.
这是她的婚礼 她一生中最快乐的日子

130
00:07:58,740 --> 00:08:00,400
We'll see.
我们等着瞧吧

131
00:08:05,380 --> 00:08:07,280
Well, thank you for lunch.
谢谢你请我吃午餐

132
00:08:07,520 --> 00:08:09,480
Wait, I thought you paid.
等一下，我以为你付了钱

133
00:08:09,680 --> 00:08:12,410
Apparently, we don't pay for food anymore.
很明显的，我们不必再掏钱买食物了

134
00:08:15,390 --> 00:08:18,020
-Do you see what I see? -It's still there.
-我没有看错吧？ -它还在那里

135
00:08:19,090 --> 00:08:21,390
Mrs. Braverman must be out.
布雷曼太太一定是出去了

136
00:08:25,200 --> 00:08:28,170
She could be out of town. Maybe gone for months.
她可能出城去了 或许几个月后才会回来

137
00:08:28,440 --> 00:08:32,000
By then, it may spoil. She can't come back to bad cheesecake.
到时候蛋糕一定坏了 不能让她回来时看到坏掉的起司蛋糕

138
00:08:32,210 --> 00:08:34,140
-It could kill her. -Don't want that.
-她可能会中毒死掉 -我不希望发生那种事

139
00:08:34,410 --> 00:08:35,530
We're protecting her.
我们是在保护她

140
00:08:35,780 --> 00:08:37,000
-We'll take it. -But quick.
-我们把它拿走 -但是快一点

141
00:08:37,280 --> 00:08:39,140
-Why? -I hear her in there.
-为什么？ -我听到她在里面走动的声音

142
00:08:39,410 --> 00:08:41,780
Go! Go! Go!
快走…

143
00:08:45,820 --> 00:08:47,650
Oh, my God, that's David.
天啊，是大卫

144
00:08:47,920 --> 00:08:49,820
-Who? -David, the scientist guy.
-谁？ -那个科学家大卫

145
00:08:50,060 --> 00:08:52,030
David that I was in love with.
我爱上的那个大卫

146
00:08:52,230 --> 00:08:54,790
Who went to Russia and broke my heart, David.
他到俄国去，伤了我的心，大卫

147
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:56,050
Oh, my God!
我的天啊！

148
00:08:56,330 --> 00:08:58,630
Say their name enough, they turn around.
只要一直念某人的名字 那个人就会转过身来

149
00:09:00,800 --> 00:09:02,030
Phoebe.
菲比

150
00:09:02,300 --> 00:09:04,240
David.
大卫

151
00:09:06,810 --> 00:09:09,870
What are you doing? Aren't you supposed to be in Russia?
你在做什么？你不是在俄国吗？

152
00:09:10,140 --> 00:09:12,870
I'm just in town for a conference.
我到城里来开会

153
00:09:13,080 --> 00:09:15,670
God, you look phenomenal.
天啊，你看起来美得出奇

154
00:09:15,950 --> 00:09:17,350
Well...
喔…

155
00:09:17,550 --> 00:09:18,810
Yeah.
对

156
00:09:19,490 --> 00:09:22,390
You look great too. Did you get a haircut?
你看起来也很棒，你剪了头发吗？

157
00:09:22,660 --> 00:09:25,180
Yeah. Well, I got like 30 of them.
对，我大概剪了三十次

158
00:09:26,960 --> 00:09:29,160
Look, I got a confession to make.
听着，我得跟你坦诚一件事

159
00:09:29,400 --> 00:09:31,660
I was hoping to run into you here.
我希望能在这里遇到你

160
00:09:31,870 --> 00:09:35,670
I didn't know if I should call. I was only in town a few days...
我不知道该不该打电话给你 我只会在城里待几天…

161
00:09:35,870 --> 00:09:38,340
and I didn't want to intrude on your life.
我不想打扰你的生活

162
00:09:38,540 --> 00:09:40,400
I really wanted to see you...
我真的想见你…

163
00:09:40,680 --> 00:09:43,580
but I didn't know if you wanted to see me.
但我不知道你要不要见我

164
00:09:44,410 --> 00:09:48,910
Of course I would want to see you. I think about you all the time.
我当然想见你，我常常想到你

165
00:09:49,120 --> 00:09:52,090
Really? Because I think about you all the time.
真的吗？因为我也常常想到你

166
00:09:52,350 --> 00:09:56,380
There's a statue in Minsk that reminds me of you so much.
明斯克有一座雕像，让我常常想起你

167
00:09:56,620 --> 00:09:58,850
It's actually of Lenin...
事实上那是列宁的雕像…

168
00:09:59,060 --> 00:10:02,290
but, you know, at certain angles...
但有些角度…

169
00:10:03,100 --> 00:10:05,730
Anyway, do you want to have dinner tonight?
总之，今晚你想跟我共进晚餐吗？

170
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:07,300
Yes.
好

171
00:10:07,600 --> 00:10:09,230
Oh, no!
喔，不！

172
00:10:10,200 --> 00:10:11,730
-What? -I can't.
-什么？ -我不能

173
00:10:12,010 --> 00:10:15,240
I can't believe I have plans. Can you do it tomorrow?
我不敢相信 我有约了，明天可以吗？

174
00:10:15,440 --> 00:10:20,040
No, I have to go in a few hours. I have to be on the redeye.
不，再过几小时我就得离开 我得赶回去

175
00:10:20,310 --> 00:10:22,940
Listen, next time you're in Minsk...
听着，下次你到明斯克…

176
00:10:23,280 --> 00:10:26,520
Phoebe? Can I talk to you for a second?
菲比，我能跟你谈一谈吗？

177
00:10:26,750 --> 00:10:28,220
What are you doing?
你在做什么？

178
00:10:28,460 --> 00:10:29,920
I have plans with Joey.
我跟乔伊有约

179
00:10:30,160 --> 00:10:31,720
So? He'll understand.
所以呢？他会谅解的

180
00:10:31,930 --> 00:10:34,620
No, he won't. And that's not even the point.
不，他不会的，那根本不是重点

181
00:10:34,830 --> 00:10:39,960
I made a whole speech about how you do not cancel plans with friends.
我教训他不该见色忘友

182
00:10:40,740 --> 00:10:43,930
And now just because, potentially,  the love of my life...
现在只因为可能是我真爱的人…

183
00:10:44,170 --> 00:10:46,440
returns from Russia for one night...
明天就要回俄国去…

184
00:10:46,670 --> 00:10:49,470
I should change my beliefs?
我就应该改变我的想法？

185
00:10:49,740 --> 00:10:51,770
I should change my beliefs!
我应该改变我的想法！

186
00:10:52,350 --> 00:10:56,940
No. If I don't have my principles,  I don't have anything.
不，如果失去了原则 那么我什么都不会有

187
00:10:57,150 --> 00:10:58,310
You're so strong.
你太有说服力了

188
00:10:58,590 --> 00:11:02,580
Or I should rush through dinner with Joey and meet David at 9.
或许我可以赶快跟乔伊吃完晚餐 然后九点跟大卫见面

189
00:11:09,960 --> 00:11:12,190
Oh, my God, that is so good!
我的天啊，那真的是太棒了！

190
00:11:12,470 --> 00:11:15,900
I'm full. And yet I know if I stop eating this...
我吃饱了，但我知道 如果我现在停下来…

191
00:11:16,170 --> 00:11:17,760
I'll regret it.
我会后悔

192
00:11:19,570 --> 00:11:21,540
Hey, what have you got there?
嘿，你们在吃什么？

193
00:11:21,810 --> 00:11:23,170
Oh, it's...
喔，那是…

194
00:11:23,410 --> 00:11:25,680
It's tofu cake. Want some?
豆腐蛋糕，你要吃一点吗？

195
00:11:29,880 --> 00:11:31,720
What are you doing tonight?
今晚你要做什么？

196
00:11:32,090 --> 00:11:34,210
Dude. Dude.
兄弟

197
00:11:35,420 --> 00:11:36,860
Sorry.
对不起

198
00:11:37,090 --> 00:11:38,750
I got plans with Phoebe.
我跟菲比有约

199
00:11:38,960 --> 00:11:41,860
Really? Monica said she had a date at 9.
真的？摩妮卡说她九点有约会

200
00:11:42,030 --> 00:11:44,730
-What? Tonight? -That's what Monica said.
-什么？今晚？ -摩妮卡是那么说的

201
00:11:44,970 --> 00:11:49,600
After that speech, she makes a date on the same night she has plans with me?
她教训了我一顿 却同时约了我跟她的男伴？

202
00:11:49,800 --> 00:11:52,530
She's trying to pull a fast one on Big Daddy.
她想草草解决大爹地

203
00:11:58,550 --> 00:12:01,040
Here, I think this is us.
好了，我们的位置应该是这一桌

204
00:12:02,180 --> 00:12:04,810
Limited seating, my ass.
座位有限，我的天啊

205
00:12:05,020 --> 00:12:07,110
Let's see who made the cut.
我们来看看谁被邀请了

206
00:12:07,320 --> 00:12:09,290
Hi. I'm Monica Geller.
嗨，我是摩妮卡盖勒

207
00:12:09,490 --> 00:12:12,950
-How do you know the bride and groom? -I worked with Frannie.
-你们跟新人是什么关系？ -我是芬妮以前的同事

208
00:12:13,190 --> 00:12:15,490
Used to work with her. Used to.
以前的同事，以前

209
00:12:15,760 --> 00:12:18,030
I'm a relative and I didn't get invited.
我是她的亲戚却没有被邀请

210
00:12:18,300 --> 00:12:20,670
A blood relative. Blood.
我是她的血亲，血

211
00:12:22,340 --> 00:12:25,270
Stop saying "blood" to strangers.
别在陌生人面前提到“血”

212
00:12:26,070 --> 00:12:28,410
And you? How do you know the couple?
你呢？你跟快乐的新人是什么关系？

213
00:12:28,640 --> 00:12:30,870
We went to college with both of them.
我们是他们的大学同学

214
00:12:31,080 --> 00:12:33,170
Now we live next door.
现在是他们的邻居

215
00:12:33,380 --> 00:12:34,870
Okay, you're fine.
好吧，你还够格

216
00:12:39,690 --> 00:12:41,810
-Are you guys ready? -Yes.
-你们要点菜了吗？ -是的

217
00:12:42,060 --> 00:12:46,320
I'll have a green salad,  house dressing and water's fine.
我要沙拉，特调酱汁，给我水就好了

218
00:12:46,660 --> 00:12:48,090
And for you, sir?
你呢？先生

219
00:12:48,360 --> 00:12:50,960
Yeah. This slow-roasted salmon...
对，慢烤鲑鱼…

220
00:12:51,130 --> 00:12:52,660
how slow are we talking?
那到底有多慢呢？

221
00:12:53,670 --> 00:12:55,830
It's already been roasted.
它已经烤好了

222
00:12:56,100 --> 00:12:59,870
Oh, then no. Maybe I should hear the specials again.
那么我不要，麻烦你 再告诉我一次今日特餐

223
00:13:00,140 --> 00:13:02,740
We've heard the specials three times.
我们已经听了三次

224
00:13:02,980 --> 00:13:06,970
There's prime rib, mahi-mahi and a very special lobster ravioli.
有烤肋排，鬼头刀鱼 跟特制龙虾饺子

225
00:13:07,250 --> 00:13:11,880
-Actually, we're out of the ravioli. -Well, that changes everything!
-事实上我们没有饺子了 -那我们得重来一次

226
00:13:13,520 --> 00:13:16,320
You know what, Phoebe? You were right before.
你知道吗？菲比 之前你说的话是对的

227
00:13:16,620 --> 00:13:18,620
Friends are so important.
朋友太重要了

228
00:13:18,860 --> 00:13:21,120
Yeah, I'm very wise. I know.
对，我很聪明，我知道

229
00:13:21,430 --> 00:13:22,920
Know what I really want?
你知道我想做什么吗？

230
00:13:23,200 --> 00:13:26,360
-What? -Is to have a long, long talk.
-什么？ -我想花时间跟你长谈

231
00:13:26,600 --> 00:13:30,540
You know? Get Joey out on the open road and really open him up.
你知道吗？告诉我多一点人生道理

232
00:13:31,640 --> 00:13:33,400
-Any progress? -Yes.
-可以点菜了吗？ -是的

233
00:13:34,110 --> 00:13:36,410
I will have the lobster ravioli.
我要点龙虾饺子

234
00:13:37,240 --> 00:13:39,580
God, Joey, this is taking forever.
天啊，乔伊，这得花一辈子的时间

235
00:13:39,850 --> 00:13:41,410
-What's the rush? -Well...
-干嘛这么急呢？ -喔…

236
00:13:41,650 --> 00:13:44,280
I have an appointment.
我有个约会

237
00:13:44,490 --> 00:13:46,390
And it's very important.
它非常重要

238
00:13:46,620 --> 00:13:47,850
What is it?
怎么说？

239
00:13:48,720 --> 00:13:49,980
Well...
喔…

240
00:13:50,260 --> 00:13:51,620
it's a date.
我约了一个男人

241
00:13:51,890 --> 00:13:56,420
A date? No, you must be mistaken, because you wouldn't have a date...
你约了男人？不，你一定弄错了 因为你不能跟男人约会…

242
00:13:56,660 --> 00:13:59,290
on the same night you have plans with a friend.
同时又跟朋友约吃饭

243
00:13:59,570 --> 00:14:01,400
Don't make me feel badly.
别让我觉得内疚

244
00:14:01,600 --> 00:14:03,070
No, I'm gonna!
不，我就是要那么做！

245
00:14:04,610 --> 00:14:08,300
You made me feel really guilty about going out with that girl.
我跟那个女孩出去 你让我觉得非常内疚

246
00:14:08,510 --> 00:14:12,450
Like I did something terrible. Now you're doing the same thing.
好像我做了什么可怕的事 现在你也那么做

247
00:14:12,650 --> 00:14:14,940
It's not! It's totally different!
才怪，这完全不一样！

248
00:14:15,150 --> 00:14:18,380
This is with David. Remember David, the scientist guy?
我跟大卫有约 你还记得科学家大卫吗？

249
00:14:18,620 --> 00:14:20,180
He's very special to me.
对我来说他非常特别

250
00:14:20,450 --> 00:14:23,950
My girl the other night was special. She was a scientist too.
那晚我约的女孩也很特别 她也是个科学家

251
00:14:24,190 --> 00:14:27,060
-She was? -Well, she graduated high school.
-是吗？ -她高中毕业

252
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:29,660
Whatever. Know what?
随便啦，你知道吗？

253
00:14:29,930 --> 00:14:33,490
He's only here for four hours and I'm gonna go see him.
他只会在这里待四小时，我得去见他

254
00:14:33,700 --> 00:14:35,430
-Fine! -Yeah.
-好吧 -对

255
00:14:37,640 --> 00:14:41,630
What are you still doing here? I told you, lobster ravioli!
你还在这里做什么？ 我说过了，龙虾饺子！

256
00:14:45,410 --> 00:14:48,310
I was about to leave. I didn't think you were coming.
我正要离开，我以为你不会来了

257
00:14:48,520 --> 00:14:50,810
I wouldn't have missed this.
我绝不会错过这次约会

258
00:14:51,150 --> 00:14:53,140
Well, I'm very glad you're here.
我很高兴你来了

259
00:14:53,650 --> 00:14:55,820
Oh, you're such a gentleman.
你是个绅士

260
00:14:56,060 --> 00:14:58,120
Come on, we're going to my place.
来吧，到我家去

261
00:15:04,930 --> 00:15:07,420
Are you eating the cheesecake without me?
你想一个人独吞起司蛋糕？

262
00:15:10,470 --> 00:15:13,700
I will give you $100 to whistle right now.
只要你现在能吹出口哨 我就给你一百块

263
00:15:18,480 --> 00:15:21,070
-How can you eat it without me? -What'll you do?
-你怎么可以不管我一个人独吞？ -你会怎么做呢？

264
00:15:21,350 --> 00:15:25,310
Tell Monica or Joey? No, you'd have to tell them everything.
告诉摩妮卡或乔伊？ 不，你得把一切都告诉他们

265
00:15:25,550 --> 00:15:29,390
We're dessert stealers. We're living outside the law.
我们是甜点小偷，我们犯了法

266
00:15:29,590 --> 00:15:31,890
I don't trust you with this cake.
我不能让你跟蛋糕独处

267
00:15:32,090 --> 00:15:34,530
I got it first,  and I'm taking it back!
我先发现它的，我要把它拿回来！

268
00:15:34,760 --> 00:15:37,600
-What? Oh, no. -Oh, yes.
-什么？不 -对

269
00:15:38,100 --> 00:15:40,460
You think I trust you with it?
你以为我就能相信你吗？

270
00:15:40,700 --> 00:15:42,230
No, we'll split it.
不，我们平分它

271
00:15:42,470 --> 00:15:44,270
That's not fair. You had some.
那不公平，你已经吃掉一点了

272
00:15:44,540 --> 00:15:47,370
I think Monica would be very interested to know...
我想摩妮卡一定想知道…

273
00:15:47,610 --> 00:15:50,540
that you called her cheesecake "dry and mealy."
你说她做的起司蛋糕“又干又粗”

274
00:15:50,780 --> 00:15:52,970
What do we use to split it?
我们要用什么来切蛋糕？

275
00:15:55,580 --> 00:15:57,550
All right, pick a half.
好了，挑一块

276
00:15:58,620 --> 00:16:01,710
Well, this side looks bigger.
这块比较大

277
00:16:02,920 --> 00:16:06,090
But there's more crust on this side.
但这块饼干比较多

278
00:16:06,360 --> 00:16:08,060
Maybe if I measure it..
或许我该量一下…

279
00:16:08,300 --> 00:16:09,490
Pick a piece!
快挑一块

280
00:16:09,730 --> 00:16:13,600
-All right, I pick that one. -It's the smaller piece.
-好吧，我挑那一块 -那一块比较小

281
00:16:14,270 --> 00:16:16,200
Okay. There you go.
好了，拿去吧

282
00:16:16,440 --> 00:16:19,430
Enjoy your half, my friend. But that is it.
好好享受你的蛋糕吧 我的朋友，因为大势已定

283
00:16:19,640 --> 00:16:23,010
No sharing, no switching,  and don't come crying to me...
我不会跟你分，不会跟你换 别哭着跑来找我…

284
00:16:23,210 --> 00:16:25,540
if you eat your piece too fast.
如果你一下子就把蛋糕吃完了

285
00:16:36,120 --> 00:16:39,820
-You gonna give me some of yours? -Oh, no.
-你要给我一点蛋糕吗？ -不

286
00:16:40,130 --> 00:16:44,260
No switching, no sharing. And don't come crying to me.
我不会跟你分，不会跟你换 别哭着跑来找我

287
00:16:44,630 --> 00:16:47,400
I may just sit here and have my cake all day.
我要坐在这里 花一整天好好享用我的蛋糕

288
00:16:47,630 --> 00:16:50,730
Just sit here in the hallway and eat my..
我要坐在走廊上吃我的…

289
00:17:02,620 --> 00:17:04,580
Ross, sweetheart!
罗斯，甜心！

290
00:17:04,820 --> 00:17:06,680
Oh, hey, Aunt Millie.
嘿，米莉阿姨

291
00:17:06,950 --> 00:17:10,950
-Isn't it a beautiful wedding? -Yes, it is.
-这个婚礼很温馨吧？ -没错

292
00:17:15,300 --> 00:17:17,560
Every time, on the lips!
她每次都亲嘴巴！

293
00:17:17,800 --> 00:17:19,700
Why? Why on the lips?
为什么？为什么要亲嘴巴？

294
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:25,560
There's Frannie. Won't she be happy to see me?
芬妮在那边，她看到我 一定会很高兴吧？

295
00:17:25,810 --> 00:17:27,640
You be nice, all right?
你得乖乖的，好吗？

296
00:17:27,840 --> 00:17:30,170
I didn't bring you to ambush her.
我不是带你来欺负她

297
00:17:30,440 --> 00:17:33,570
Frannie was the one who showed your Playboys to Mom.
芬妮把你的《花花公子》拿给妈妈看

298
00:17:33,810 --> 00:17:35,780
That bitch.
那个死小孩

299
00:17:40,120 --> 00:17:41,310
Monica!
摩妮卡！

300
00:17:41,590 --> 00:17:42,780
What..?
什么…？

301
00:17:43,020 --> 00:17:45,460
Am I doing here? Surprised to see me?
我在这里做什么？ 你看到我很讶异吗？

302
00:17:45,690 --> 00:17:48,090
Ross brought me. How do you like that?
罗斯带我来的，你还喜欢吗？

303
00:17:48,300 --> 00:17:50,790
Hi, Frannie. Congratulations.
芬妮，恭喜

304
00:17:52,600 --> 00:17:55,800
You invite my whole family, and not me? Why?
你邀请我的家人 却不邀请我，为什么？

305
00:17:56,040 --> 00:17:59,490
Why wouldn't you want me here? What could I have done?
你为什么不希望我来？我做了什么？

306
00:18:01,110 --> 00:18:02,870
Stuart!
史都华！

307
00:18:03,410 --> 00:18:05,900
I believe you know my husband.
我相信你认识我丈夫

308
00:18:07,210 --> 00:18:11,410
So it's really a question of "who" could you have done.
问题应该是，你把上了“谁”

309
00:18:20,060 --> 00:18:22,430
I hate this, but I have to go.
我讨厌这样，但我得走了

310
00:18:22,660 --> 00:18:24,820
I can't miss my flight.
我不能错过飞机

311
00:18:25,070 --> 00:18:27,400
I bet there's another flight to Minsk in..
我敢说下一班飞往 明斯克的飞机是在…

312
00:18:27,670 --> 00:18:29,360
July.
七月

313
00:18:38,850 --> 00:18:41,580
That's really beautiful. What does it mean?
那真的好窝心，它是什么意思？

314
00:18:41,850 --> 00:18:44,370
"Please clean my beakers."
“请帮我把杯子洗干净”

315
00:18:45,090 --> 00:18:47,020
I don't get out of the lab much.
我不常离开实验室

316
00:18:49,720 --> 00:18:52,280
I thought it meant something else.
我以为它有别的意思

317
00:18:52,560 --> 00:18:56,090
Yeah, well, I really actually wanted to say...
对，事实上，我想说…

318
00:18:56,360 --> 00:18:57,850
that.
那个

319
00:18:58,100 --> 00:19:01,530
But I figured I probably shouldn't because...
我想或许我不该说，因为…

320
00:19:02,540 --> 00:19:04,270
I have to leave.
我得离开

321
00:19:04,540 --> 00:19:07,030
No, you're right. Don't say it.
不，你说的对，别说

322
00:19:08,710 --> 00:19:10,900
I do, though.
但我真的那么想

323
00:19:12,980 --> 00:19:14,450
I do too.
我也是

324
00:19:23,220 --> 00:19:25,050
Well, bye, Phoebe.
再见，菲比

325
00:19:36,200 --> 00:19:39,930
Now's not the time, Joey. You can yell at me tomorrow.
现在不是时候 乔伊，明天你可以骂我

326
00:19:40,210 --> 00:19:42,970
Wait, no, Phoebe. I'm not gonna yell at you.
等一下，不，菲比 我不会骂你

327
00:19:43,240 --> 00:19:45,800
I just started thinking about you and David...
我只是开始想到你跟大卫…

328
00:19:46,080 --> 00:19:50,240
and I remember how bummed you were the first time he left.
我记得他第一次离开时你有多难过

329
00:19:52,490 --> 00:19:54,480
Oh, Phoebe, come here.
菲比，过来

330
00:19:55,320 --> 00:19:58,950
-Are you okay? -No, I'm not okay.
-你还好吧？ -不，我一点都不好

331
00:19:59,330 --> 00:20:03,020
The only guy I've ever been crazy about is going to Minsk...
我唯一喜欢的男人要去明斯克…

332
